a&amp;author=EA+Zeikus&amp;author=D+Levine&amp;author=NM+Rofsky&amp;publication_year=2007&amp;journal=RadioGraphics&amp;pages=721-743&amp;doi=10.1148%2Frg.273065116&amp;pmid=17495289">Google Scholar</a></div></div></div></div></div><div role="listitem" data-has="label"><div class="label">8.</div><div id="b8-0291781" class="citations"><div class="citation"><div class="citation-content">Patel SJ, Reede DL, Katz DS, Subramaniam R, Amorosa JK. Imaging the pregnant patient for non-obstetric conditions: algorithms and radiation dose considerations. <em>RadioGraphics</em> 2007;27:1705–1722.</div><div class="external-links"><div class="core-xlink-crossref"><a href="https://doi.org/10.1148/rg.276075002">Crossref</a></div><div class="core-xlink-pubmed"><a href="https://pubmed.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/18025513/">PubMed</a></div><div class="core-xlink-google-scholar"><a href="https://scholar.google.com/scholar_lookup?title=Imaging+the+pregnant+patient+for+non-obstetric+conditions%3A+algorithms+and+radiation+dose+considerations&amp;author=SJ+Patel&amp;author=DL+Reede&amp;author=DS+Katz&amp;author=R+Subramaniam&amp;author=JK+Amorosa&amp;publication_year=2007&amp;journal=RadioGraphics&amp;pages=1705-1722&amp;doi=10.1148%2Frg.276075002&amp;pmid=18025513">Google Scholar</a></div></div></div></div></div><div role="listitem" data-has="label"><div class="label">9.</div><div id="b9-0291781" class="citations"><div class="citation"><div class="citation-content">Singh AK, Desai H, Novelline RA. Emergency MRI of acute pelvic pain: MR protocol with no oral contrast. <em>Emerg Radiol</em> 2009;16:133–141.</div><div class="external-links"><div class="core-xlink-crossref"><a href="https://doi.org/10.1007/s10140-008-0748-8">Crossref</a></div><div class="core-xlink-pubmed"><a href="https://pubmed.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/18649091/">PubMed</a></div><div class="core-xlink-google-scholar"><a href="https://scholar.google.com/scholar_lookup?title=Emergency+MRI+of+acute+pelvic+pain%3A+MR+protocol+with+no+oral+contrast